                    .col-sm-8.description-container
                      .description.readable.no-inline-characters.no-inline-symbols.no-inline-terms
                        %p.theme-text2
                          The gods actively intervene in the lives of the mortals, often using the characters like chess pieces to carry out their own power struggles.
                          %span.inline-character Juno
                          hates the Trojans and does her best to stop
                          %span.inline-character Aeneas
                          from fulfilling his destiny, even setting up the war that fills the second half of the poem.
                          %span.inline-character Venus
                          tries to protect and help her son.
                          %span.inline-character Neptune
                          just gets annoyed that some other god thinks he can mess with the ocean…
                        %em
                          %a{:href => "/lit/the-aeneid/themes/the-gods-and-divine-intervention"} (read full theme analysis)
